    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-19T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="217"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119 P 43/910: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Special Representative</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-19T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 19, 1918—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. [From President Wilson.] Referring to your 119,<note n="11" xml:id="d217fn11">
                        <ref target="frus1919Parisv01#pg_160">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                            160</ref>.</note> shall try to get Miss Tarbell to go over.</p>
                <p>Referring to your 120,<note n="12" xml:id="d217fn12">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_297">p. 297</ref>.</note> I
                    entirely approve, and hope that you will in my name urge the acquiescence of the
                    Supreme Command. This seems to me essential to a peaceful settlement. Woodrow
                    Wilson.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
